{"title":"Shovel Research Nitto Rack Strut Light Mount","link":"https://theradavist.com/shovel-research-nitto-rack-strut-light-mount/","date":1705075337000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"5000\" height=\"4000\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/7mm-box-pink.jpg?fit=1200,4000&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/7mm-box-pink.jpg?w=5000&amp;quality=75 5000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/7mm-box-pink.jpg?resize=1200,960&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/7mm-box-pink.jpg?resize=2000,1600&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/7mm-box-pink.jpg?resize=768,614&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/7mm-box-pink.jpg?resize=1536,1229&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/7mm-box-pink.jpg?resize=2048,1638&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p><em>If you have a Nitto rack and are looking to mount a generator or USB charging light to the struts, <a href=\"https://shovelresearch.com/7mm-nitto-compatible-light-mount\" target=\"_blank\">Shovel Research</a> just adapted its <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/shovel-research-rod-steward-review/\" target=\"_blank\">Rod Steward</a> light mounts to Nitto’s 7mm strut diameter…</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"4000\" height=\"3200\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/7mm-on-strut.jpg?fit=1200,3200&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/7mm-on-strut.jpg?w=4000&amp;quality=75 4000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/7mm-on-strut.jpg?resize=1200,960&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/7mm-on-strut.jpg?resize=2000,1600&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/7mm-on-strut.jpg?resize=768,614&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/7mm-on-strut.jpg?resize=1536,1229&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/7mm-on-strut.jpg?resize=2048,1638&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>These are the exact same simple light mount, but made to mount to Nitto adjustable rack struts, which have a diameter of 7mm. These won’t work for non-adjustable nitto racks, which should have mounting points already, so you wouldn’t need one anyway.</p>\n<p>Light mounts include a machined clip, a 20mm M5 bolt, and one double threaded stand-off. The M5 side secures the clip to the rack strut, and the M6 side is for you to bolt on your light. If you use a button-head M6 bolt, both bolts will use a 4mm hex key, which is very n i c e.</p>\n<p>Material: 6061-T6 aluminum<br />\nFinish: anodized silver (clear) or black<br />\nWeight: 12 grams</p>\n<p>See more at <a href=\"https://shovelresearch.com/7mm-nitto-compatible-light-mount\" target=\"_blank\">Shovel Research</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/shovel-research-nitto-rack-strut-light-mount/\">Shovel Research Nitto Rack Strut Light Mount</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"caf9aaa7cee00c05de89e32e6670e771053d85c266e4585039d4542278bd8a3d","category":"Cycling"}